reviewText: Needs sample datasets to really learn powerbi
i do not feel , i learn through this course all the functions were known . it's a very basics course instead of doing this course i would prefer to spend time on power bi application.
This course has no labs or sample data sets. A PowerBI license is also required so unless your company has powerBI you can't even take this course.

This is competently done for what it is. But it IS NOT A LIVE COURSE. It's a voice synthesizer mostly reading steps for very specific tasks. Hearing a human who understands the material talking about it MATTERS. This is just a cheap way to fake that. And the laziness shows because there are  just introductory statements followed by the step-by-step crap. No human speaking from actual understanding. This would be OK for free content with a few ads. But I'm paying for Coursera and in this course Coursera is not giving me the expected value for my money.

I thought to go through this course to gain knowledge of Power BI to get better response and hike in any company. For that purpose a person needs practical knowledge of any data visualization tool. I have covered the domain of one and a half week of this course and it's totally thoeritical, no any practical process of explaining the preocess of going through the Power BI tool. That theoritical knowledge could also may help to crack  the interview (not all but yeah it could help in some interview). And the questions being asked to score 80% are like, you have to mug up and vomit it.Please upgrade the process, I came here because I've heard a lot about coursera. Perhaps its like I've been the victim of coursera now you also have to be.And please give us the optio to give negative star also. 1 satr is least to opt for.
A​ human instructor would make the course much better!

The course was good in terms of introduction to Power Bi and navigating  the application interface, but that's where it ends, no hands-on approach. I expected a practical illustration or a dataset to download and work with as we go along the course module but I was disappointed because I stayed long thinking we will eventually get hands on a dataset to practice alongside the video instructions. If you want to practical approach to learning Power BI, this course is not for you

This course would really benefit from an included data set.Also, it would be helpful for the videos to give examples of situations where different features would be useful to use rather than just quickly running through how to use them.

The title seems to be not applicable because the course does not involve anything about data-driven decisions. The course focuses on introduction, navigation and familiarization of the tool.
Course did not provide datasets/materials. I wanted to spend my limited available study time learning about Power BI, not scavenging for datasets.
